cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "excubitor"
abstract: >-
  Safety fences for autonomous coding agents: stdlib-only Python
  hooks plus Agent Skills-format capability packets that let an LLM
  agent work unattended without trusting it to bless its own work.
  Provides mechanical version-control guards, loop discipline, and a
  falsifiable intent-record (telos) system. The guard's decision core
  is runtime-neutral - a second, non-Claude-Code adapter drives the
  same code under an equivalence test - so its portability is
  demonstrated rather than asserted.
type: software
